The United Arab Emirates has agreed to resume visa issuance to Nigerians, the government has said. Hadi Sirika, Minister of Aviation, announced this via his Twitter handle on Wednesday.  He disclosed that the move was to allow Emirates Airlines resume operations in Nigeria He said, “UAE has written to state that they agree to issue visas to Nigerians, consequently decision has been reached to allow Emirates to fly into Nigeria. “Commencement of the Visa issuance is condition precedent. Please bear with this unusual situation. Many thanks.” See Also






